class Solution {
public:
    bool hasCycle(ListNode *head) {
        ListNode* fast = head;
        ListNode* slow = head;
        while(fast!=NULL && fast->next!=NULL){
            fast = fast->next->next;
            slow = slow->next;
            if(slow==fast) return true;
        }
        return false;
    }
};


"Idea:
Use two pointers: slow and fast, both starting from the head of the linked list.
The slow pointer moves one step at a time, while the fast pointer moves two steps at a time.
If the linked list contains a cycle, the fast pointer will eventually catch up to the slow pointer.
Traverse the list while fast and fast->next are not NULL to avoid invalid access.
Inside the loop, move slow by one node and fast by two nodes.
If at any point slow == fast, it means a cycle exists, so return true.
If the loop ends because fast reaches NULL, the list has no cycle, so return false.
Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)
"
